# 1. 新しい日常

Rui: Okay... I think I have everything I need for today.
Rui: Oh, I could use those lights for the final scene too.
Rui: Hehe. Time to put on another fantastic show!
Tsukasa: Argh!
Tsukasa: That flash of light... What was it?!
Nene: You remember now, don't you, Black Knight? You used to wield your sword to protect people, to keep peace.
Emu: So those shinies were his memories coming back? It looked so pretty!
Tsukasa: You're right... I'd forgotten what was really important to me.
Tsukasa: I shall vow to only ever brandish my sword in the name of peace as I had in the past!
Rui: The Black Knight was once again back on the righteous path and peace returned to the world.
Miku: What a terrific story! Maybe I could play a part too♪
Tsukasa: Hah hah hah! I'm not surprised!
KAITO: The light effect at the end deserves a special mention. It was a very clever lighting scheme!
Rui: Hehe, so it was worth the effort.
Miku: And the part where Tsukasa leaps almost up to the ceiling was so awesome♪
Emu: I loved that bit too! You shot up like a rocket, Tsukasa! It was so cool♪
Nene: I thought he was going to go through the roof.
Tsukasa: Ah, yes. Being lifted up by hidden wires... To be honest, I was scared senseless.
Tsukasa: But you need to challenge yourself to make extraordinary performances! And I aim to be the world's greatest star!
Tsukasa: If it's for the sake of entertaining my audience, I'll pull off even the most dangerous stunts with elegance and grace!
Rui: Well, well, it's certainly great to have a reliable guy such as yourself on the team.
Rui: I'm thinking of adding in a new part, especially for a star of your caliber. What do you say?
Tsukasa: Ah, a new part...?!
Emu: What sort of thing do you have in mind? Is it gonna be fun?
Nene: I have a bad feeling about this...
Rui: Don't worry, I've made due considerations for health and safety. Although that performance may require some courage.
Len: Hey, guys!
Emu: Hmm? Who's that?
Miku: That's Len! Hey, Leeen!
Nene: Like... Kagamine Len?
Len: Yup, that's me! Nice to meet you all♪
Len: I was coming to see your show, but on the way here, I saw some plushies having an argument.
Len: By the time I got them to calm down and make up, the show was over! I'm so gutted that I missed it...
KAITO: I was wondering where you were. It's a pity you couldn't make it.
Rui: Hmm... I feel sorry for Len missing out. Why don't we do another performance for him?
Emu: YEESSS! I'll even do it a hundred times!
Nene: A hundred might be a bit much...
Nene: But I suppose we could do it once more. It'll be good practice...
Tsukasa: Then it's settled! Feast your eyes on our wonderful show!
Len: Awesome! Everyone, thank you so much!
Emu: Aah, I had TONS of fun! And Len really liked our show too!
Nene: Yeah. We also got some pointers for improvement.
Tsukasa: Our big performance tomorrow is guaranteed to be a resounding success!
Rui: Yes, I'm sure it will go without a hitch... It might be time to start thinking of what our next show after that will be.
Nene: Already?
Rui: Why not? I already have some new ideas to play around with to make our next show even more entertaining.
Emu: Is that possible?! I'm so hyped♪
Tsukasa: You'll have me doing even trickier stunts, huh...?
Nene: Shouldn't you be pleased? It'll give you the attention you so badly crave, Mr. Self-proclaimed Star.
Tsukasa: I think you meant to say acclaimed star!
Emu: It's going to be so amazing, Tsukasa! Every show Rui comes up with is so much fun!
Tsukasa: Fun, yes... But I'd rather not have a jetpack strapped to my back again, or anything like that.
Rui: Not your cup of tea, Tsukasa...?
Rui: It would make for a truly fantastic spectacle, worthy of a true star such as...
Tsukasa: Alright, fine...! I'll do whatever you need me to do!
Tsukasa: If it's to put on a good show, then I'll do anything!
Tsukasa: As long as you can promise me that whatever antics you have me do will make the audience roar with delight.
Rui: Hehe, you can be sure of that.
Rui: It's definitely going to be a crowd-pleaser of the highest caliber.
Rui: Ascending to the stage from the seats won't have enough of an impact. He needs to make a powerful impression as a knight...
Rui: Oh, I've got it! That will definitely be better! But I'll have to assess its practicality and safety first.
Nene: Hehe...
Nene: You look like you've been having the time of your life lately.
Rui: Oh, have I?
Nene: Yeah. You look like you're having fun. Before, you...
Rui: What do you mean, Nene?
Nene: You seemed bored all the time before, but now you keep making this weird face.
Rui: How is it weird? Should I be concerned?
Rui: Jokes aside, you may be right... I'm finally living my life.
Rui: Being able to put my ideas into action feels amazing.
Rui: Anyways, the stage is sorted and we're ready to hold our show. I'll start planning the next one in the meantime.
Rui: Hmm... Maybe I can make it easier for Tsukasa by reusing some of the gimmicks that worked with him last time.
Nene: Hehe... I'm happy for you, Rui.
Tsukasa: Alright! Let's get started with the rehearsal...!
Mascot: Miss!
Emu: Hm? What's up?
Mascot: A notice about an event that's to be held here just came in...!
Emu: An event? Dad didn't mention anything about that...
Emu: What sort of event is it?
Mascot: Here's the flyer.
Emu: Let's see... The First Phoenix Show Contest...?
Tsukasa: Did you just say Show Contest...?!
